Title: Intelligent Database Environment for Advanced Applications IDEA CPT/OnLine: Accessing Chimera Databases via the World Wide Web  
Note: Copyright 1997 University of Bonn ESPRIT Project 6333 Page 1  
Abstract: Summary: Within the IDEA prolongation phase, the transfer of Chimera technology to the World-Wide Web has been the major overall goal. In this context, we investigated several approaches for making the Chimera Prototyping Tool (CPT) developed at the University of Bonn accessible via the Web. Whereas graphical schema design turned out to be too hard to provide with the currently available means, we designed and implemented a data manipulation and querying interface for accessing existing Chimera databases via the Web. CPT/OnLine provides such access to Chimera databases using the CPT. This document describes architecture and usage of CPT/OnLine. Author(s): Thomas Lemke Contributor(s): Rainer Manthey Issued by: Rainer Manthey University of Bonn Department of Computer Science III Romerstr. 164; D-53117 Bonn; Germany Tel. +49 / 228 / 73 - 4292 Authorised by: Rainer Manthey Issue number: 1 Status: DEFINITIVE Date of issue: 21.3.1997 Reference: IDEA.DE.22.O.011 Number of pages: 13 
