Reference-contexts: Although the focus of the IDEA group at the University of Bonn for the prolongation phase was on the completion of our Chimera tools, we decided to investigate the possibility to make our Chimera tools | especially the Chimera Prototyping Tool <ref> [GLM96] </ref> | accessible via the Web. For this sake, we evaluated several possibilities for providing database functionality over the internet with respect to their feasibility in the context of the IDEA prolongation phase. <p> Having opened a specific database, the first DML page is offered to the user (figure 4). The main part of this page is the text area where the user may type in a Chimera data manipulation command in the syntax as it is accepted by the CPT <ref> [GLM96, GL96] </ref>. This command must be closed by a semicolon (;). The "Clear Command" button resets the text area.
